Replaces the deferred placeholders in
docs/qa-reports/qa-review-evidence/sample-{rejection,pass}.md with
actual claude-sonnet-4-6 outputs from the live Railway prod deploy:

- sample-rejection.md: 5-MCQ kakapo paper with 3 deliberately-broken
  items (wrong answer / unanswerable / two-correct-options).  Verdict
  came back reject as expected; Claude's summary correctly identifies
  the wrong-answer and unanswerable items.  Token cost $0.0208.

- sample-pass.md: 5-MCQ paper sourced from real Cambridge IELTS 8
  Test 4 Passage 3 (Q31-Q35).  Verdict came back needs_review (not
  pass).  The flagged ambiguity in Q4 'Separate containers for
  individual specimens' is real, not a false-positive ŌĆö calibration
  data, documented as a follow-up.  Token cost $0.0224.

Both runs surface a tool-use quirk where the issues array is empty
even though the summary describes specific issues; the verdict
itself is correct so the dashboard still routes the paper to the
right queue, but the per-issue evidence quotes are missing.
Documented as a follow-up.

docs/qa-reports/railway-e2e-verification.md is the broader E2E pass:
- /api/health 200
- AI short-answer grading (3/3 + 0/3 cases) returns calibrated marks
- Excel attendance export streams a real .xlsx with 3 sheets
- Attendance scan endpoints correctly blocked by IpAllowlistGuard
  (sandbox is off school WiFi ŌĆö verified the gate fires before
  validation runs)
- RBAC matrix: teacher denied on student-only / admin-only routes,
  empty/missing/wrong-secret JWTs all 401
- CORS allowlist: no ACAO echoed for evil/non-allowlisted origins
- JWT_SECRET is NOT the .env.example default (verified by signing a
  forged token with that exact string and getting 401)
- Cross-class IDOR + browser UI render skipped with explicit reasons
  (only one class in prod; Chrome MCP not connected)

Real Anthropic spend on this verification: ~$0.05 USD.

