+# Railway E2E Verification ŌĆö 2026-05-09
+
+End-to-end verification of the prod Railway deployment of `exam-paper-system`
+at `https://exam-paper-system-production.up.railway.app`, run from a sandbox
+shell that does NOT have Chrome-extension or school-WiFi access. Every test
+was issued via `curl` against the live API; no mocks. Each section records
+the exact request, the verbatim response (or HTTP status + body excerpt), and
+a Pass / Fail / Skipped verdict with the blocker named when skipped.
+
+| # | Test | Verdict |
+|---|---|---|
+| 1 | Health-check / deployment confirmation | Ō£ģ Pass |
+| 2 | AI QA review ŌĆö deliberately broken paper ŌåÆ `reject` | Ō£ģ Pass (verdict correct; sub-finding documented) |
+| 3 | AI QA review ŌĆö Cambridge real paper ŌåÆ not-`reject` | ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ  Partial (`needs_review`, not `pass` ŌĆö see ┬¦3) |
+| 4 | AI short-answer auto-grading | Ō£ģ Pass |
+| 5 | Excel attendance/scores export (.xlsx, 3 sheets) | Ō£ģ Pass |
+| 6 | Student scan-roster + scan endpoints | ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ  WiFi-gate blocks sandbox (which is the right answer) |
+| 7 | Cross-class IDOR | ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ  Skipped ŌĆö would require resetting a real student password |
+| 8 | Role-based access control (RBAC) on REST endpoints | Ō£ģ Pass |
+| 9 | CORS allowlist | Ō£ģ Pass |
+| 10 | JWT signature / dev-secret protection | Ō£ģ Pass |
+| 11 | Browser UI rendering of IELTS 7-task widgets | ŌÜĀ’ĖÅ  Skipped ŌĆö Chrome MCP returned `[]` connected browsers |
+
+Running cost (real Anthropic spend on this verification): ~**$0.043** for the two QA-review calls + two short-answer-grading calls.
+
